SIMPLE: orgy
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Orgy
<hw>Or"gy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu>sing. <plw>Orgies</plw>
<pr>(<?/)</pr></plu>. <ety>[F. <ets>orgie</ets>, <ets>orgies</ets>, L.
<ets>orgia</ets>, pl., Gr. <?/; akin to <?/ work. See <er>Organ</er>,
and <er>Work</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>A sacrifice accompanied by certain ceremonies in
honor of some pagan deity; especially, the ceremonies observed by the
Greeks and Romans in the worship of Dionysus, or Bacchus, which were
characterized by wild and dissolute revelry. Usually in the plural
form.</def> <note>[The singular is rarely used in this
sense.]</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>As when, with crowned cups, unto the Elian god,⟦br⟧
Those priests high <qex>orgies</qex> held.</q>
<rj><qau>Drayton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Wild, drunken, or licentious revelry; an uninhibited
carouse.</def> <rj><au>B. Jonson.</au> <au>Tennyson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A series of sexual activities involving more than
two couples in a group.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <specif>Hence:</specif> <def>An event characterized by
unrestrained indulgence in passion; <as>as, an <ex>orgy</ex> of buying
of internet stocks</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Orgillous</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Orgy
<hw>Or"gy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Orgies</plw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>.</plu> <def>A frantic revel; drunken
revelry. See <er>Orgies</er></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Orgyia</ent>⟦br⟧
